  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7</p>\n<p>Boil a full kettle</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>conchiglie</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for an initial 4 min</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2186.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2186.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2186.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2186.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2186.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>cauliflower<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into small florets </p>\n<p>After 4 min, add the <strong>cauliflower florets</strong> to the <strong>pasta</strong> and cook for a further 6-7 min or until everything is cooked with a slight bite</p>\n<p>Once cooked, drain, reserving 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml] </span><strong>starchy cooking water</strong> and leave to steam dry in the sieve </p>\n<p>Reserve the pot</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2186.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2186.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2186.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2186.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2186.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the pasta cooks, grate the <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>\n<p>Combine the <strong>grated cheese</strong> with the <strong>panko breadcrumbs </strong>– these are your<strong> cheesy breadcrumbs</strong></p>\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the<strong> garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2186.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2186.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2186.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2186.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2186.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pot to a medium heat with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>butter</strong></p>\n<p>Once hot, add 1 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> cook for 1 min or until a sandy paste forms</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong> and whisk until smooth</p>\n<p>Once smooth, remove the pot from the heat and add the <strong>crème fraîche</strong>, <strong>Dijon mustard</strong> and a grind of <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2186.-step-4-new-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2186.-step-4-new-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2186.-step-4-new-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2186.-step-4-new-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2186.-step-4-new-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained pasta</strong> <strong>and cauliflower</strong> to the<strong> sauce</strong> and stir it all together – this is your <strong>creamy cauliflower pasta</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2186.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2186.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2186.-step-5-x700.jpg",
